        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 4 at 6:57PM MDT by NWS Glasgow MT</headline>
        <description>At 656 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 9
miles east of Intake, or 19 miles north of Wibaux, moving northeast
at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

This storm will remain over mainly rural areas of northeastern
Wibaux, eastern Dawson and southeastern Richland Counties.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
